  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6757 sitting just above the massive negative gamma wall at 6755 (-8B), dealers are in forced buying mode as any dip toward 6755 triggers amplified buying pressure to hedge their short gamma exposure. The PIN regime suggests dealers will continue this stabilizing behavior, but the concentration of negative gamma between 6745-6765 creates a volatile pocket where small moves get magnified. Key level is the 6724 flip strike - any break below flips dealers to negative gamma selling, while a push toward 6800 max positive gamma will trigger dealer selling pressure.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile chop between 6755-6765 with dealers buying every dip until we break 6724.",
